CLOCK_MODE().details: Machine-readable description of the clock as specified in EIP-6372. Has been overridden to inform callers that this contract uses timestamps instead of block numbers, to match `clock()`

approve(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-approve}. NOTE: If `amount` is the maximum `uint256`, the allowance is not updated on `transferFrom`. This is semantically equivalent to an infinite approval. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

clock().details: Clock used for flagging checkpoints. Has been overridden to implement timestamp based checkpoints (and voting).

decimals().details: Returns the number of decimals used to get its user representation. For example, if `decimals` equals `2`, a balance of `505` tokens should be displayed to a user as `5.05` (`505 / 10 ** 2`). Tokens usually opt for a value of 18, imitating the relationship between Ether and Wei. This is the default value returned by this function, unless it's overridden. NOTE: This information is only used for _display_ purposes: it in no way affects any of the arithmetic of the contract, including {IERC20-balanceOf} and {IERC20-transfer}.

decreaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: Atomically decreases the allowance granted to `spender` by the caller. This is an alternative to {approve} that can be used as a mitigation for problems described in {IERC20-approve}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address. - `spender` must have allowance for the caller of at least `subtractedValue`.

delegate(address).details: Delegate votes from the sender to `delegatee`.

delegates(address).details: Get the address `account` is currently delegating to.

getPastTotalSupply(uint256).details: Retrieve the `totalSupply` at the end of `timepoint`. Note, this value is the sum of all balances. It is NOT the sum of all the delegated votes! Requirements: - `timepoint` must be in the past

getPastVotes(address,uint256).details: Retrieve the number of votes for `account` at the end of `timepoint`. Requirements: - `timepoint` must be in the past

getVotes(address).details: Gets the current votes balance for `account`

increaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: Atomically increases the allowance granted to `spender` by the caller. This is an alternative to {approve} that can be used as a mitigation for problems described in {IERC20-approve}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

params.minters: the addresses that are allowed to mint
params.mintingAllowances: the amount of tokens that each minter is allowed to mint

name().details: Returns the name of the token.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params.from: the address whose allowedFrom status is being set

setAllowedFromPermissionless(address,boo.details: this function is callable by anoyone in the harness

params.from: the address whose allowedFrom status is being set

params.to: the address whose allowedTo status is being set

symbol().details: Returns the symbol of the token, usually a shorter version of the name.

totalSupply().details: The issued supply of EIGEN should match the bEIGEN balance of this contract, less any bEIGEN tokens that were sent directly to the contract (rather than being wrapped)

transfer(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transfer}. Requirements: - `to` cannot be the zero address. - the caller must have a balance of at least `amount`.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transferFrom}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. This is not required by the EIP. See the note at the beginning of {ERC20}. NOTE: Does not update the allowance if the current allowance is the maximum `uint256`. Requirements: - `from` and `to` cannot be the zero address. - `from` must have a balance of at least `amount`. - the caller must have allowance for ``from``'s tokens of at least `amount`.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

allowedFrom(address).notice: mapping of addresses that are allowed to transfer tokens to any address

allowedTo(address).notice: mapping of addresses that are allowed to receive tokens from any address

bEIGEN().notice: CONSTANTS & IMMUTABLESthe address of the backing Eigen token bEIGEN

disableTransferRestrictions().notice: Allows the owner to disable transfer restrictions

initialize(address,address[],uint256[],u.notice: An initializer function that sets initial values for the contract's state variables.

mint().notice: This function allows minter to mint tokens

mintAllowedAfter(address).notice: STORAGEmapping of minter addresses to the timestamp after which they are allowed to mint

mintingAllowance(address).notice: mapping of minter addresses to the amount of tokens they are allowed to mint

multisend(address[],uint256[]).notice: Allows the sender to transfer tokens to multiple addresses in a single transaction

setAllowedFrom(address,bool).notice: This function allows the owner to set the allowedFrom status of an address

setAllowedFromPermissionless(address,boo.notice: This function allows the owner to set the allowedFrom status of an address

setAllowedTo(address,bool).notice: This function allows the owner to set the allowedTo status of an address

totalSupply().notice: Overridden to return the total bEIGEN supply instead.

transferRestrictionsDisabledAfter().notice: the timestamp after which transfer restrictions are disabled

unwrap(uint256).notice: This function allows Eigen holders to unwrap their tokens into bEIGEN

wrap(uint256).notice: This function allows bEIGEN holders to wrap their tokens into Eigen
